KATSINA – No fewer than a total of 12,747 have graduated from the BATCs, School of Agriculture, Youth Empowerment Programme and Federal Labour Trade Test Grade III certificate to obtain various skills acquisition training in Katsina State. Similarly, more than 16,000 persons have graduated from the Youth Craft Village, including university and polytechnic graduands within the last four years of the APC led administration. Governor Aminu Bello Masari, represented by Alhaji Hussaini Adamu Karaduwa, the state Special Adviser, Directorate of Employment Promotion and Vocational Training, disclosed this at the presentation of starter packs to graduands of the 2017 National Industrial Skills Development Programme (NISDP) in Katsina on Wednesday.